<concept id="concept_E8D43EB4494E41D2AB42D4A89396D1AB"
            xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>Prerequisites and Preparation</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p>The following sections describe the prerequisites that must be fulfilled and the preparations you need to take before installing <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/>. </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Hardware and Operating Systems</title>
            <p><ph
                conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/> can be installed on a host machine with the following operating systems:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7.3 (for Intel64). </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7.4 (for Intel64). </p>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <note othertype="note"
                    >Make sure that you use a clean operating system. This avoids compatibility-related issues during the installation of <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/>.</note>
            <p>As underlying platform technology, the following OpenStack platforms are supported:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Red Hat Enterprise Linux OpenStack Platform 10</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <p>The following hardware resources are recommended: </p>
            <table
                colsep="1" frame="all"
                    rowsep="1">
                <tgroup
                        cols="2">
                    <colspec
                        colname="col2" colnum="1"
                        colwidth="1*"/>
                    <colspec
                        colname="col3" colnum="2"
                                colwidth="2.32*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry
                                colname="col2">Hardware type</entry>
                            <entry
                                colname="col3">Description</entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry
                                colname="col2">Model</entry>
                            <entry
                                colname="col3">
                                <p>Fujitsu Server PRIMERGY RX300 S8 </p>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry
                                colname="col2">CPU</entry>
                            <entry
                                colname="col3">
                                <p>Intel® Xeon® E5-2660 v2, 2.20 GHz or more</p>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry
                                colname="col2">Memory</entry>
                            <entry
                    colname="col3">
                                <p>64 GB DIMM (DDR3) or more</p>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </section>
        <section>
            <p><ph
                conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/> without any data requires about 2 GB of disk space. The disk capacity required for log data and metrics data varies considerably depending on the number of services and servers to be monitored.</p>
            <p>Make sure that enough disk space is provided. If required, mount partitions for storing the log data and the metrics data. The default installation uses the following directories: </p>
            <ul
            id="The_data_directory_of_Elastic_concept_conbody_section_3_ul">
                <li>The data directory of Elasticsearch is located in <codeph>/var/data/elasticsearch</codeph>.</li>
                <li>The data directory of InfluxDB is located in <codeph>/var/opt/influxdb/data</codeph>. </li>
                <li>The data directory of MariaDB is located in <codeph>/var/lib/mysql</codeph>. </li>
                <li>The data directory of Kafka is located in <codeph>/var/kafka</codeph>.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Web Browsers</title>
            <p><ph
                conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/> has been tested with the following Web browsers: </p>
            <ul id="Google_Chrome_50.0_concept_conbody_section_2_ul">
                <li>Google Chrome 50.0</li>
                <li>Microsoft Internet Explorer 11.0 (with Compatibility View disabled)</li>
                <li>Mozilla Firefox 46.0</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </conbody>
</concept>
